    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spring greens</strong>, then rip the leaves off, discard the tough stalks, and layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced spring greens</strong> to a large baking tray (or two!) and sprinkle with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 1 tsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>sugar</strong> and a large drizzle of <strong>vegetable</strong> <strong>oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
