          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> drained</strong> <strong>udon noodles</strong> to the pan with the <strong>pak choi green tops</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the noodles are coated in sauce</p><p>Place the <strong>Chinese-style pancakes</strong> (still in their bag) in the microwave and heat for 30 secs to steam</p><p>Once ready, remove the <strong>roasted five-spice duck leg[s]</strong> from the oven, shred using two forks and mix <strong>half</strong> the <strong>shredded duck</strong> (save the rest for later!) through the noodles – these are your <strong>Shanghai-style noodles</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
